modules.description: This module manages an asynchronous terminal interface for rendering images and handling input events. It provides functions to create and manipulate a terminal context, set images, move the cursor, and handle resize events. Concrete use cases include building interactive terminal UIs with real-time updates and input handling.

This module provides an asynchronous interface for managing terminal rendering and input handling. It supports creating and manipulating a terminal context, setting images, moving the cursor, and responding to resize events. Key data types include terminal contexts and images, with operations for real-time updates and event-driven interaction. Example uses include building dynamic, interactive terminal applications like text editors or visualizers.
